{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/vop/DASH--discrete-1.0/DASH-discrete-icon.svg", "type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "discrete", "version": "1.0", "namespace": "DASH"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Discrete"], "extent": [39, 50]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Perform integer division, quantization, and modulo with the rounding method of choice."], "extent": [50, 146]}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 0, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--discrete-1.0/DASH-discrete-help_basics.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [146, 198], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Outputs derived from Floor, explained with a practical example of filling cups with juice."], "extent": [198, 300]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [300, 312], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Value"], "extent": [312, 321], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Quantity to discretize."], "extent": [321, 350]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unit"], "extent": [350, 356], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reference scale to divide ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, " by. E.g., at ", {"type": "code", "text": ["2.0"]}, ", a ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, " of ", {"type": "code", "text": ["5.7"]}, " will be indexed to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["2.0"]}, ", instead ", {"type": "code", "text": ["5.0"]}, "."], "extent": [489, 616]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "unit_s7"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rounding Limit"], "extent": [616, 632], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Threshold limit for ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, "'s fractional part, that will determine if the rounding will be to the previous or the next index. E.g., a limit of ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.3"]}, " will index a ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, " of ", {"type": "code", "text": ["5.4"]}, " to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["6"]}, ", since ", {"type": "code", "text": ["*.4"]}, " is to the right of the limit.\n    While this enables a custom rounding routine, it\u2019s basically a blend between the habitual rounding methods:"], "extent": [647, 997]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["1.0"]}, ": ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/floor", "type": "link", "text": ["Floor"], "fallback_text": "floor()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/floor.html"}, ". Default.", {"tag": "br", "attrs": {}, "type": "xml", "text": ""}, "\n    ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.5"]}, ": ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/rint", "type": "link", "text": ["Round"], "fallback_text": "rint()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/rint.html"}, {"tag": "br", "attrs": {}, "type": "xml", "text": ""}, "\n    ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0.0"]}, ": ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/ceil", "type": "link", "text": ["Ceil"], "fallback_text": "ceil()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/ceil.html"}], "extent": [997, 1102]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "limit"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mirror"], "extent": [1102, 1110], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Rounding on the negative side will mirror the positive side. As it happens with ", {"scheme": "Vex", "value": "/vex/functions/trunc", "type": "link", "text": ["Truncate"], "fallback_text": "trunc()", "fullpath": "/vex/functions/trunc.html"}, " or ", {"type": "code", "text": ["int()"]}, " casting."], "extent": [1126, 1256]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "mirror"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Inclusive"], "extent": [1256, 1267], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Determines if the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Limit"]}, " value itself will be rounded to the previous(", {"type": "em", "text": ["off"]}, ") or the next index(", {"type": "em", "text": ["on"]}, "). Only relevant when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Limit"]}, " is neither ", {"type": "code", "text": ["0"]}, " or ", {"type": "code", "text": ["1"]}, ", and can be a rare occasion."], "extent": [1286, 1476]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "inclusive"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Presets"], "extent": [1476, 1485], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["These buttons set ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Limit"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Mirror"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Inclusive"]}, " parameters so that the rounding operation matches the label."], "extent": [1485, 1609]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [1609, 1617], "body": [{"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 0, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--discrete-1.0/DASH-discrete-help_rounding_patterns.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [1617, 1680], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["All rounding options at play producing common rounding routines."], "extent": [1704, 1780]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"display": "wide left"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Array Auto Resize"], "extent": [1780, 1806], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Common Size"], "extent": [1806, 1819], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Determines the size that all input arrays will have. ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Min"]}, " will use the smallest array\u2019s size, while ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Max"]}, " will use the greatest array\u2019s size."], "extent": [1848, 1998]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_size"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill"], "extent": [1998, 2004], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["Sized up arrays need a fill value. This determines whether the fill is the parameter\u2019s ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Default"]}, " or, if the array is not empty, its ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Last"]}, " or ", {"type": "em", "text": ["First"]}, " value."], "extent": [2033, 2193]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "array_autoresize_fill"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "extent": [2193, 2203], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Description"], "extent": [2203, 2216], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 2, "text": ["String to display info on top of the node in the network view. The pilcrow \u00b6 button enables multi-line text."], "extent": [2235, 2351]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "description"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "outputs", "container": true, "type": "outputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2351, 2360], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["index"]}], "extent": [2360, 2370], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Integer division of ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, "/", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Unit"]}, ". How many times does ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Unit"]}, " fully fit into ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, " depending on how its rounded."], "extent": [2385, 2514]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "index"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["quantize"]}], "extent": [2514, 2526], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Decimation/Quantization of the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, ", i.e. ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Unit"]}, " times ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["index"]}]}, ". "], "extent": [2544, 2625]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "quantize"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["modulo"]}], "extent": [2625, 2635], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Remainder of integer division, i.e. ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Value"]}, " minus the ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["quantize"]}]}, "."], "extent": [2651, 2728]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "modulo"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["oscillate"]}], "extent": [2728, 2741], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Odd ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["index"]}]}, " regions will have a downward slope modulo, resulting in a zig-zag, oscillating pattern."], "extent": [2760, 2873]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "oscillate"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["umodulo"]}], "extent": [2873, 2884], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Unlike ", {"type": "ui", "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["modulo"]}]}, ", this is always in the range [0 to 1). Its comparison against ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Limit"]}, " is what determines if the rounding index goes to the next or previous integer."], "extent": [2901, 3086]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "umodulo"}}], "container": true}, {"type": "fig_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "fig", "indent": 0, "text": [" ", {"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/vop/DASH--discrete-1.0/DASH-discrete-help_outputs.svg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "role": "item", "extent": [3086, 3139], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "tex